    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A masonry unit, laid so that its ends are exposed, overlapping two or more adjacent wythes of masonry and tying them together.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000010761/Harris, Dictionary of Architecture and Construction (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Unidad de mampostería colocada de modo que sus extremos queden expuestos, traslapando dos o más filas adyacentes de mampostería y uniéndolas entre sí.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
